{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4e746e37-8d98-4f09-b4e9-032da1ef92a8","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Update package references** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Upgrade xUnit packages** — MTP requires **xUnit v3**:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Replace xunit 2.9.3 -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps).\n\n**Key xUnit v2 → v3 migration notes:**\n- `Xunit` namespace → some types moved; most test code works as-is.\n- `[Fact]`, `[Theory]`, `[InlineData]` remain the same.\n- `Assert` API is largely unchanged.\n- `IClassFixture<T>` / `ICollectionFixture<T>` still work.\n- If you use `xunit.analyzers`, upgrade to the v3-compatible version bundled with `xunit.v3`.\n\nCheck the [xUnit v3 migration guide](https://xunit.net/docs/getting-started/v3/migration) for any breaking changes specific to your usage.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10d11ac7-36fe-4f47-8392-28ae57761cb8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":488,"requestId":"9851:875F:1533E9:1BD7DC:69FFD731"},"id":"50619f29-c982-43f4-bd5d-11c7e35d7273","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:19.760Z","parentId":"aa1c5e79-fa20-434d-9e03-51e480091bf7"}
